In [12]:
from pathlib import Path

# Settings
image_shape = (224, 224) #(height, width) not (width, height)
image_save_path = Path('./saved_spectrogram.png')

# Load audio file as Audio object
audio = Audio.from_file('300_AUDIO.wav')

# Create Spectrogram object from Audio object
spectrogram = Spectrogram.from_audio(audio)

# Convert Spectrogram object to PIL Image
image = spectrogram.to_image(shape=image_shape)

# Save image to file
image.save(image_save_path)

import zipfile
import tarfile

import glob
files = glob.glob("/Users/renkil/MSCS/CV/dataset/dcapswoz.ict.usc.edu/wwwedaic/data/*.tar")

for file in files:

from pathlib import Path
import glob
from matplotlib.backends.backend_agg import FigureCanvasAgg as FigureCanvas

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import librosa.display

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import librosa

files = glob.glob("/Users/renkil/MSCS/CV/dataset/dcapswoz.ict.usc.edu/wwwedaic/data/unzip_1/*")

count = 0
#print(files)
for file in files:
    file_name = file.split("/")[-1]
    print(count,file_name)
    count+=1

    y, sr = librosa.load(file+'/{}_AUDIO.wav'.format(file_name.split("_")[0]))
    y = y[:100000] # shorten audio a bit for speed
    image_save_path = Path('/Users/renkil/MSCS/CV/dataset/dcapswoz.ict.usc.edu/wwwedaic/data/spectogram_images/{}_spectrogram.png'.format(file_name))

    window_size = 1024
    window = np.hanning(window_size)
    stft  = librosa.core.spectrum.stft(y, n_fft=window_size, hop_length=512, window=window)
    out = 2 * np.abs(stft) / np.sum(window)

    # For plotting headlessly

    fig = plt.Figure()
    canvas = FigureCanvas(fig)
    ax = fig.add_subplot(111)
    p = librosa.display.specshow(librosa.amplitude_to_db(out, ref=np.max), ax=ax, y_axis='log', x_axis='time')
    ax.axes.get_xaxis().set_visible(False)
    ax.axes.get_yaxis().set_visible(False)
    fig.savefig(image_save_path)

from pathlib import Path
import pandas as pd
import glob
files = glob.glob("/Users/renkil/MSCS/CV/dataset/dcapswoz.ict.usc.edu/wwwedaic/data/unzip_1/*")

print(files)
text_data = []

for file in files:
    files_data = []
    image_shape = (224, 224) #(height, width) not (width, height)
    file_name = file.split("/")[-1]
    file_index = file_name.split("_")[0]
    df = pd.read_csv(file+'/{}_Transcript.csv'.format(file_index))
    text = " ".join(df["Text"].values)
    print(file_index,text)
    files_data.append(file_index)
    files_data.append(text)
    text_data.append(files_data)
    
dff= pd.DataFrame(text_data,columns=["Sample","Transcript"])
dff.to_csv("text_transcript.csv")

import sklearn
import librosa
import librosa.display

# Load the audio file
samples, sample_rate = librosa.load("/Users/renkil/MSCS/CV/dataset/dcapswoz.ict.usc.edu/wwwedaic/data/unzip_1/303_P/"+"{}_AUDIO.wav".format(303), sr=None)
mfcc = librosa.feature.mfcc(samples, sr=sample_rate)

# Center MFCC coefficient dimensions to the mean and unit variance
mfcc = sklearn.preprocessing.scale(mfcc, axis=1)
librosa.display.specshow(mfcc, sr=sample_rate, x_axis='time')

print (f'MFCC is of type {type(mfcc)} with shape {mfcc.shape}')

In [ ]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import librosa.display

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import librosa



y, sr = librosa.load("/Users/renkil/MSCS/CV/dataset/dcapswoz.ict.usc.edu/wwwedaic/data/unzip_1/680_P/"+"{}_AUDIO.wav".format(680))
y = y[:100000] # shorten audio a bit for speed

window_size = 1024
window = np.hanning(window_size)
stft  = librosa.core.spectrum.stft(y, n_fft=window_size, hop_length=512, window=window)
out = 2 * np.abs(stft) / np.sum(window)

# For plotting headlessly
from matplotlib.backends.backend_agg import FigureCanvasAgg as FigureCanvas

fig = plt.Figure()
canvas = FigureCanvas(fig)
ax = fig.add_subplot(111)
p = librosa.display.specshow(librosa.amplitude_to_db(out, ref=np.max), ax=ax, y_axis='log', x_axis='time')
ax.axes.get_xaxis().set_visible(False)
ax.axes.get_yaxis().set_visible(False)
fig.savefig('spec_1.png')
